<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Anthony Davis landed a three-pointer on the buzzer to lift the Los Angeles Lakers to a thrilling 105-103 win and a 2-0 Western Conference final series lead over the Denver Nuggets on Sunday.</p>

<p>Davis's channeled the inner spirit of former Lakers star Kobe Bryant, who seven regular-season buzzer-beaters are tied for the most ever.</p>

<p>The Lakers were wearing special 'mamba' black tribute jerseys following Bryant's tragic death in a helicopter crash in January, but his memory appeared to inspire his former side to a dramatic victory.</p>

<p>Anthony Davis landed a three-pointer on the buzzer as the LA Lakers beat the Denver Nuggets</p>

<p>Davis ended with 31 points, scoring their last 10 in the dramatic Western Conference victory</p>

<p>Davis ended with 31 points, scoring his team's last 10 in contributing a 22-point second half as the Lakers defied yet another Denver comeback.</p>

<p>LeBron James had 26 points and 11 rebounds for the Lakers, while Danny Green had 11 points.  </p>

<p>The Nuggets trailed by as many as 16 points before Nikola Jokic took control by scoring 11 straight Denver points, including a basket that put his side up 103-102 with 20 seconds left.</p>

<p>In a frantic finish, LA's Alex Caruso missed a three-pointer, before a shot from Green was blocked out of bounds with 2.1 seconds left.</p>

<p>The Lakers were wearing special 'mamba' black tribute jerseys for late Lakers star Kobe Bryant</p>

<p>Rajon Rondo then found Davis near the sideline, and the All-Star forward found the basket from long-range.</p>

<p>'Special moment for a special player. Happy to be a part of it,' said James.</p>

<p>Jokic had 30 points and nine assists for the Nuggets while Jamal Murray had 25 points.</p>

<p>Game three is on Tuesday night.</p>
